%pyspark
import numpy as np
import random
import pandas as pd
from pyjake.sparkmodule import udf_month, udf_weather
from pyspark.sql import Row
from pyspark.sql.types import DoubleType
from pyspark.sql.functions import udf
from sklearn.preprocessing import MinMaxScaler


udf_scaler = udf(lambda i: i/10000, DoubleType())

# 1-1. 데이터셋 생성하기
sz = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///sun/kasi_sun_angle.parquet')
nl = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///nl/witlab/cas/simple_srs.parquet')\
                .where('date > "2017-04-11"')
aday = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/available_days.parquet')
cl = spark.read.parquet('hdfs:///dayday/clean_days.parquet')

spdf = nl.join(sz, ['date', 'time'])\
         .where('illum > 0 and uvi > 0 and uvi < 14')\
         .withColumn('illum_s', udf_scaler('illum'))

import pandas as pd

spdf_train_b, spdf_test = spdf.randomSplit([0.7, 0.3], 3)

x_train_b = np.array(spdf_train_b.select('illum_s', 'solar_zenith').toPandas())

print('x train (bef) len:', len(x_train_b))

print('x val len:', len(x_val))
print('y val len:', len(y_val))
print('x test len:', len(x_test))

%pyspark
from pyspark.mllib.regression import LabeledPoint
from pyspark.mllib.tree import RandomForest, RandomForestModel
from pyspark.mllib.util import MLUtils

# Load and parse the data file into an RDD of LabeledPoint.
trainingData = spdf_train.select('illum_s', 'solar_zenith', 'uvi')\
                         .rdd.map(lambda r: LabeledPoint(r['uvi'], [r['illum_s'], r['solar_zenith']]))
testData = spdf_test.select('illum_s', 'solar_zenith', 'uvi')\
                    .rdd.map(lambda r: LabeledPoint(r['uvi'], [r['illum_s'], r['solar_zenith']]))

model = RandomForest.trainRegressor(trainingData, categoricalFeaturesInfo={},
                                    numTrees=128, featureSubsetStrategy="auto",
                                    impurity='variance', maxDepth=30, maxBins=64)

# Evaluate model on test instances and compute test error
predictions = model.predict(testData.map(lambda x: x.features))
labelsAndPredictions = testData.map(lambda lp: lp.label).zip(predictions)

print(predictions.collect()[:5])

testMAE = labelsAndPredictions.map(lambda lp: np.abs(lp[0] - lp[1])).sum() / float(testData.count())
testMSE = labelsAndPredictions.map(lambda lp: (lp[0] - lp[1]) * (lp[0] - lp[1])).sum() / float(testData.count())
print('test> mse:', testMSE, ', mae:', testMAE)
print('Learned regression forest model:')
print(model.toDebugString())

%pyspark
from pyspark.mllib.regression import LabeledPoint
from pyspark.mllib.tree import RandomForest, RandomForestModel
from pyspark.mllib.util import MLUtils

# Load and parse the data file into an RDD of LabeledPoint.
trainingData = spdf_train.select('illum_s', 'solar_zenith', 'uvi', 'swr')\
                         .rdd.map(lambda r: LabeledPoint(r['uvi'], [r['illum_s'], r['solar_zenith'], r['swr']]))
testData = spdf_test.select('illum_s', 'solar_zenith', 'uvi', 'swr')\
                    .rdd.map(lambda r: LabeledPoint(r['uvi'], [r['illum_s'], r['solar_zenith'], r['swr']]))

model = RandomForest.trainRegressor(trainingData, categoricalFeaturesInfo={},
                                    numTrees=128, featureSubsetStrategy="auto",
                                    impurity='variance', maxDepth=30, maxBins=64)

# Evaluate model on test instances and compute test error
predictions = model.predict(testData.map(lambda x: x.features))
labelsAndPredictions = testData.map(lambda lp: lp.label).zip(predictions)

print(predictions.collect()[:5])

testMAE = labelsAndPredictions.map(lambda lp: np.abs(lp[0] - lp[1])).sum() / float(testData.count())
testMSE = labelsAndPredictions.map(lambda lp: (lp[0] - lp[1]) * (lp[0] - lp[1])).sum() / float(testData.count())
print('test> mse:', testMSE, ', mae:', testMAE)
print('Learned regression forest model:')
print(model.toDebugString())
